claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: A flowchart depicting the study cohort of adults ≥18 years (N=18,467), exclusion criteria (n=3,347), resulting in an analyzable cohort (N=14,590) split into controls (N=12,837) and influenza cases (N=1,803), each further divided into recipients of RIV4 (n=3,047 controls; n=291 cases), SD-IIV4 (n=862; n=114), and unvaccinated (n=8,878; n=1,398). does not support the claim because the figure solely outlines participant flow and vaccination groups without any information on Flublok’s production platform, recombinant HA expression, insect cells, or BEVS.
